World Airlines Body Opposed to South African Carbon Tax, Business Day Says

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-04-05T05:24:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/world-airlines-body-opposed-to-south-african-carbon-tax-business-day-says.html
International Air Transport
Association  asked  South Africa ’s Finance Minister  Pravin Gordhan 
to scrap plans for a carbon tax, Business Day reported, citing a
letter from the IATA.  A carbon tax will seriously damage South Africa’s aviation
industry and affect tourism revenue, the Johannesburg-based
newspaper today cited a letter from Giovanni Bisignani, chief
executive officer of the IATA to Gordhan, as saying.        Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
